Adventure 1: First Steps — The Windhelm Catacombs
Campaign: Ismara's Doom — The Parks Group
 Tier: Apprentice (1 AP)
 Players: 4-6
 Estimated Play Time: 2-3 Sessions
 Reward: 700-1000 Gold per player, 1 Powerful Item, 1-2 Moderate Items, 1 Advancement Point
Companion Document: Adventure 1: Windhelm City Profile & Stat Blocks — contains the Windhelm city profile (services, shops, unique locations), city events table for downtime, persistent NPC profiles, full stat blocks for non-combat NPCs (Helgrid, Quintus, Wulfgar, Jorleif, Brunwulf, generic guards), and contingencies. All combat stat blocks are inline in this document where they're used. The companion doc is for prep and between-scene reference, not mid-game lookup.

Adventure Summary
The party arrives in Windhelm seeking treatment for the Khajiit's rotjoint. A gate guard recognizes them — his cousin serves in Winterhold's guard, and word of the Frostmere heroes traveled faster than Bjorn's cart. They're welcomed into the city as known quantities.
While Helgrid examines the Khajiit's rotjoint at the Temple of Arkay (which everyone in Windhelm calls the Temple of Talos), the first Pale Fever victim is brought in — a dockworker developing geometric ice markings on his skin. The markings look identical to the Khajiit's rotjoint scarring. The same guard who let them in witnesses this and vouches for them to Windhelm's captain of the guard: these are the people who handled the Frostmere situation. They're hired to investigate.
The investigation leads to Calixto Vividius — a collector and amateur necromancer who has been conducting experiments in the ancient Atmoran catacombs beneath the Hall of the Dead. The trail of disappearances, the sounds from below, and Calixto's own helpful suggestions all point the party toward the catacombs. He's trying to achieve true resurrection by reverse-engineering Atmoran consciousness-preservation techniques from the ruins. His meddling has activated the catacombs' ancient psychic defense wards, which scramble spatial reasoning and make navigation a disorienting nightmare.
The party must navigate the warded catacombs, survive Calixto's defenses and the awakened Draugr Guardian, confront Calixto in his workshop, and destroy his work. A satisfying, complete adventure.
The truth they won't realize for several more sessions: the Pale Fever was never Calixto's doing. He was a hack copying notation he didn't understand. The geometric marks on the living people were always Ismara's. The timing just overlapped perfectly.

