Section 4: node 8 The Climax — Calixto's Final Stand
Function: Boss fight. Calixto mid-ritual, with the Guardian as his unwilling weapon. He thinks he controls it. He doesn't.
If the party never met Calixto above ground, replace the opening of the read-aloud with: "A man stands at the far end, hunched over a crude altar of bones. He's wearing fine clothes — ruined now, stained with blood. Not armor. Not robes. The clothes of someone who belongs in a drawing room, not a crypt." Everything else plays the same. After the fight, the House of Curiosities key on his body and Viola's testimony connect him to the city above.
Read Aloud
"The fissure drops you into the largest chamber yet. Ceiling arching twenty feet above, pillars carved as warriors, iron braziers at each corner filled with dark oil. The cold freezes your breath before it leaves your lips.
Calixto stands at the far end, hunched over a crude altar of bones. The friendly collector is gone — clothes stained with blood, hands shaking as he carves notation into the skin of a bound man on the altar.
Behind Calixto, something massive looms by the cracked sarcophagus. Nine feet tall, ancient plate armor crusted with ice, a greatsword of black iron. A Draugr Crypt Guardian. Its blue-fire eyes are fixed on Calixto's back with what might be hatred. A bone-and-wire amulet around Calixto's neck pulses — keeping it in check. Barely.
Calixto hears you. He turns. His eyes are fevered.
'You don't understand. I'm so close. The Atmorans preserved consciousness for millennia and I've cracked their method. One more subject. Everything I've done — it's been for this. To bring her back.'
He's not talking to you. He's convincing himself."
