The Rumor Mill
Bjorn has heard things. He presents these at breakfast or on the way out of the city.
Path of Prophecy: "Pale road's got people standing in the fields. Not travelers — standing. Just standing there. Word is it's not just here."
Path of Steel: "Ulfric's pushing toward Whiterun. Roads west are going to be complicated."
Path of Fortune: "Jarl of Morthal's offering a bounty. Disappearances in the marshes. Locals say vampires."
Ismara, at some point during the morning, produces a note and holds it out to whoever is nearest.
It says: "West."
Living World Note — Windhelm After the Party Leaves: Ulfric's intelligence operation continues — his agents are moving through three other holds by the time the party reaches the Pale. The Pale Fever continues and Windhelm's response worsens: the quarantine is enforced against the Gray Quarter despite the disease showing no preference for Dunmer. Brunwulf's position becomes untenable. The dock network starts moving information about the frozen people along its existing channels — by Adventure 3 there is a whisper network about the phenomenon that has no accurate information but has very good geographic coverage. The party will hear echoes of Windhelm's situation in cities they haven't visited yet, carried by people they never met.

